        • [ - ] libero - member since 10-Apr-14

          I'm not sure many people saw this but Garry Rodrigues's shot was deflected by Diogo Leite's arm. While Leite was looking away (and so, had no intention to stop the ball with his arm), it could possibly be the case for a penalty, eventhough a harsh one because his arm was following the course of a natural body movement. While it seems like the 4th official was indeed saying it was a penalty, the linesman informed the referee that a Galatasaray's player offside was preceded. Therefore that's why it wasn't given a penalty. Had the referee let the game continue without giving anything, the game would restart with a dropped ball, which it didn't. They restarted a game after an offside.
